**Overall Meaning:**

"He is the companion of Lakshmi, with a unique elephant-like form, four-armed, adorned with a crescent moon. He is embodied in illusion, sweet-natured. By meditating on him and worshipping him, one acquires those same qualities."

**Explanation:**

This verse describes the physical characteristics and qualities of Ganesha, as well as the benefits of his worship. It emphasizes that he is the consort of Lakshmi, the goddess of wealth, and possesses an elephant-like form, four arms, and a crescent moon on his head. He is said to be embodied in illusion, representing the illusory nature of the world, but also possesses a sweet and benevolent nature. By meditating on him and worshipping him, devotees can acquire those same qualities, such as wealth, auspiciousness, and a kind disposition. 
